main event: Unidentified radar target observed moving at high speed over Miami, Florida on February 14, 1962.
interesting points: The object was detected by a Ground Radar Station located at Miami Air Force Base.
The radar blip showed an erratic flight pattern, making sharp turns and appearing to change shape.
The characteristics of the radar target were similar to previous reports of unidentified objects over the Miami area.
No further details were obtained about the identity or origin of the object.
